                    <h5><span class="black">Making the First String</span> <br/>2014-15</h5>
                    <p>When Madden 15 shipped, the third-year linebacker had a 64 overall rating and was buried on Denver’s bench. But after an injury to Danny Trevathan in August, Marshall joined the Broncos’ starting lineup. After he put together four straight games with a Pro Football Focus grade of +1.0 or better by midseason, Marshall was rated 75 overall with vastly increased awareness, tackling, zone coverage and play recognition ratings. By Week 14, he carried an 81 overall rating, up a league-high 17 from where he’d started the season.</p>
