                  <div class="player-bio">
                    <h5><span class="black">A Rating-Changing Moment</span><br/>Nov. 23, 2014</h5>
                    <p>A 75 overall rating for a rookie receiver is nothing to sneeze at, but that was just the beginning for the Giants wideout. Beckham recorded 31 catches in his first six games, raising his rating to an 80 overall by Week 11. And in front a national TV audience the next week, he hauled in 10 balls for 146 yards against the Dallas Cowboys -- 43 yards of which came on arguably the greatest catch in NFL history. Beckham’s rating would increase by 10 more points, and he ended the year with huge upgrades in awareness, route-running, catching in traffic -- and, of course, spectacular catch.</p>
